  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Plans and controls the execution of the project. Prepares the manpower, machinery and materials requirement on site. To confirm the duration of each critical activity and construction programme.</li>\n  <li>Regulates current activities with regards to work methods, technical solutions, resources input and other operational details.</li>\n  <li>Delegate duties to respective site personnel such as Foreman, Project Engineers, Safety Officer, Quantity Surveyor and Site Clerk.</li>\n  <li>Co-ordinates matters pertaining to site progress. Manpower and machinery utilisation, mobilisation schedule, certification of payment, site disputes, planning of site facilities and workers quarters etc.</li>\n  <li>Communicates and maintains public relation with relevant parties and local authorities.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and compile site progress reports for progress claims and monitoring project activities.</li>\n  <li>To verify work done by subcontractors.</li>\n  <li>To carry out other site works job duties as instructed.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Candidate to possess Bachelor’s Degree in Civil Engineering and relevant certificates.</li>\n  <li>At least 5 years of working experience in the construction field.</li>\n  <li>Preferably with Class 3 Driving licence.</li>\n  <li>Good interpersonal and communication skills. Leadership, problem-solving and multi-tasking skills.</li>\n</ul>",
